```ts
type ToArray<T> = T extends unknown ? T[] : never;

type R = ToArray<string | number>;
```

questions.explanation:
A conditional type whose checked type is a **naked type parameter** is *distributive*: it is applied to each member of the union independently, then the results are re-unioned. So:

```ts
ToArray<string | number>
// => ToArray<string> | ToArray<number>
// => string[] | number[]
```

To get the non-distributive `(string | number)[]`, disable distribution by wrapping both sides in a one-element tuple so the parameter is no longer "naked":

```ts
type ToArray<T> = [T] extends [unknown] ? T[] : never;
// ToArray<string | number> => (string | number)[]
```

